<subSubSection id="C3776556ED3F385BFF78FC9BFD6BFC72" pageId="622" pageNumber="623" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED3F385BFF78FC9BFD6BFC72" blockId="622.[136,778,649,2070]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED3F385BFF78FC9BFEFBFCAE" bold="true" box="[189,318,853,879]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED3F385BFF14FCB6FF3CFC50" box="[209,249,888,913]" italics="true" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">tect</emphasis>
(=a roof) and 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED3F385BFE72FCB9FE13FC50" box="[439,470,887,913]" italics="true" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">fer</emphasis>
(=carry), referring to the presence of a dorsal tergite on the genital somite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED3F385BFF78FC75FBE5FC8C" pageId="622" pageNumber="623" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED3F385BFF78FC75FF12FA12" blockId="622.[136,778,649,2070]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED3F385BFF78FC75FE08FC14" bold="true" box="[189,461,955,981]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFDFDFC75FD70FC14" box="[568,693,955,981]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421A</figureCitation>
) stout, inflated; bodylength 1.52 mm. Prosome unsegmented, 1.26 mm long, about twice as long as wide, slightly depressed, dorsoventral depth in middle 0.57 mm. In dorsal and ventral views (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFE35FB8DFD53FB9F" box="[496,662,1091,1118]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421B, D</figureCitation>
), anterior part of prosome bearing 2 weak lateral constrictions delimiting cephalosome, firstpedigerous somite, and remaining part of prosome. Free urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFD4FFB67FCC7FB02" box="[650,770,1193,1219]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421C</figureCitation>
) small, occupying about 20% of body length, consisting of genital somite and 3 abdominal somites; defined only by weak ventral and lateral constrictions; ornamented by numerous minute spinules on ventral surface. Genital somite characteristically with dorsal tergite (indicated by arrowheads in 
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFEA4FABBFDC6FA51" box="[353,515,1397,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421A, C</figureCitation>
). Anal somite bilobed posteriorly, incorporating caudal rami; caudal setae absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED3F385BFF78FA12FD38F8AD" blockId="622.[136,778,649,2070]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFEFDFA15FE71FA37" box="[312,436,1499,1526]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421E</figureCitation>
) large, elongate, about 1.8 times longer than wide (126×71 μm), with thick wall and rounded apex. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFE68F9D1FDDEF9FB" box="[429,539,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421F</figureCitation>
) small, 3-segmented; first segment broad and unarmed; second segment also broad and ornamented with many setules; thirdsegment much narrower than proximal segments, subdivided proximally, armed with several longer setules (or setae). Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFF3EF907FEB6F925" box="[251,371,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421G</figureCitation>
) 3-segmented, moderately slender; coxaandbasisunarmed; endopod (last segment) about 2.6 times longer than wide (47×18 μm); armed with 7 smallsetae (
<quantity id="4C959B38ED3F385BFEDEF8FEFE8CF88B" box="[283,329,1840,1866]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="622" pageNumber="623" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
middle, 2 subdistal, and 2 distal) plus short terminal claw, about one-third as long as endopod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED3F385BFF78F8BAFC02FD9E" blockId="622.[136,778,649,2070]" lastBlockId="622.[810,1452,173,982]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">
Labrum small, not covering mouthparts (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFD42F8BAFD3BF84F" box="[647,766,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421D</figureCitation>
). Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFED5F858FE54F871" box="[272,401,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421H</figureCitation>
) unsegmented, without suture between coxa and basis; exopod and endopod also fused with basis; proximal part (coxa) bearing short, truncate gnathobase with setulose medial margin; exopod armed with 5 setae (outermost seta small, one-thirdaslongas other 4 setae); basis-endopod with 7 setae (3 medial and 4 distal). Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFBC9FF3FFBB1FECA" box="[1036,1140,241,267]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="623.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[236,1340,212,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-18@623.[208,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="623" captionText="FIGURE 421. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); B, cephalosome, dorsal; C, urosome, dorsal view showing tergite on genital somite (arrowhead); D, cephalosome and anterior pedigerous somites, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, mandible; I, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D, E, 0.05 mm; F–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592162/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 421I</figureCitation>
) armed with 5 distinct setae on arthrite, 1 on epipodite, 2 on basis, 4 on exopod, and 3 on endopod; coxalacking endite; all setae densely pinnate, setae on exopod much larger than others. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFABBFE99FCAFFE52" captionStart="FIGURE 422" captionStartId="624.[136,245,1159,1185]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,214,1072]" captionTargetId="figure-338@624.[136,1451,191,1089]" captionTargetPageId="624" captionText="FIGURE 422. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, right leg 1; D, left leg 1; E, right leg 2. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592164/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 422A</figureCitation>
) 5-segmented; syncoxa with 5 setae grouped as 1, 2, and 2 on first to third endites; basis with 1 seta only; endopod with 1, 1, and 3 setae on first to third segments, respectively; proximal seta on syncoxa and 1 seta on third endopodal segment naked, all other setae pinnate. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFC72FDEDFBEBFDFC" box="[951,1070,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 422" captionStartId="624.[136,245,1159,1185]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,214,1072]" captionTargetId="figure-338@624.[136,1451,191,1089]" captionTargetPageId="624" captionText="FIGURE 422. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, right leg 1; D, left leg 1; E, right leg 2. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592164/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 422B</figureCitation>
) as small lobe bearing 2 pinnate setae apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED3F385BFC9AFDA6FB15FCEA" blockId="622.[810,1452,173,982]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">
Legs 1 and 2 rudimentary. Leg 1 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFAC6FDA9FA66FD43" box="[1283,1443,615,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 422" captionStartId="624.[136,245,1159,1185]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,214,1072]" captionTargetId="figure-338@624.[136,1451,191,1089]" captionTargetPageId="624" captionText="FIGURE 422. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, right leg 1; D, left leg 1; E, right leg 2. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592164/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 422C, D</figureCitation>
) represented by 2 setiferous lobes; outer lobe tipped with small secondary lobe and armed with 7 setae; inner lobe smaller than outer and armed with 2 setae. Leg 2 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED3F385BFABBFD03FCA3FCC8" captionStart="FIGURE 422" captionStartId="624.[136,245,1159,1185]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,214,1072]" captionTargetId="figure-338@624.[136,1451,191,1089]" captionTargetPageId="624" captionText="FIGURE 422. Adrodelphys tectifera gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, right leg 1; D, left leg 1; E, right leg 2. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592164/files/figure.png" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Fig. 422E</figureCitation>
) represented by small lobe bearing 2 or 3 setae and 1 isolated outer seta. Legs 3-5 absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED3F385BFC9AFCFDFBE5FC8C" blockId="622.[810,1452,173,982]" box="[863,1056,819,846]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED3F385BFC9AFCFDFC59FC8C" bold="true" box="[863,924,819,845]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED3F385BFC9AFC9BFB6EFC14" pageId="622" pageNumber="623" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED3F385BFC9AFC9BFB6EFC14" blockId="622.[810,1452,173,982]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED3F385BFC9AFC9BFC09FCAE" bold="true" box="[863,972,853,879]" pageId="622" pageNumber="623">Remarks</emphasis>
. The coxal gnathobase of the mandible has an unarmed medial margin and appears non-functional in the adult female. The morphology of the preceeding developmental stages is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
